data.name: Pork Gravy with Red Wine and Fresh Herbs
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and flavorful pork gravy enhanced with red wine and aromatic fresh herbs, perfect for drizzling over mashed potatoes or roasted vegetables.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a saucepan, heat the pork drippings over medium heat until sizzling.
Add minced garlic and saut√© for about 30 seconds until fragrant.
Pour in the red wine and bring to a simmer, scraping any brown bits from the bottom of the pan.
After 5 minutes, add the chicken broth and fresh herbs. Stir well and bring to a gentle boil.
In a small bowl, mix cornstarch with a little water to form a slurry, then gradually whisk it into the gravy.
Continue to simmer until the gravy thickens to your desired consistency, about 10-15 minutes.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste before serving.
